Advanced Practice Providers (APPs) are a group of healthcare professionals licensed to practice in a collaborative agreement with a physician in their area of expertise. NPs and PAs receive additional education and training in their areas of expertise. This allows them to perform many of the same tasks as a physician: ordering tests, prescribing medications, diagnosing illnesses, conducting physical examinations, and more.
